 at Berkeley (generously funded by Joan and Peter Avenali), or Berkeley’s Una’s Lecturer (endowed in the memory of Una Smith Ross, Class of 1911); several are based on other events presented by the center over the years, such as the “Humanities Perspectives on Aging” program or the “Futures” lecture series organized to commemorate the center’s tenth anniversary. All are the reflection of a public event before a live audience. We have chosen to retain references to the live event where they occur, though space limitations would not permit the inclusion of audience questions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aAppiah, Kwame Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarshay, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoetzee, J. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanto, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrafton, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenblatt, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHass, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeaney, Seamus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIgnatieff, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlíma, Ivan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaqueur, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, Maya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollan, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaitowitz, Stanley, 